eport is saved to a local file and delivery is retried on the next scheduled run.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Behavior spans network failure handling plus persistence across scheduled executions. Realistic failures often depend on process boundary/OS execution context (path, permissions, working dir, run-to-run state), so Integration can miss them. Agentic/Workflow are rejected because behavior is delivery fallback orchestration, not model-decision quality or multi-agentic sequencing.","test_description":"Run script in an environment where email endpoint is actually unreachable (or blocked) and confirm fallback file is written; then run the next scheduled invocation with email restored and assert the saved report is retried and delivered, with retry state cleared afterward.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.08,"Integration":0.3,"System":0.55,"Agentic":0.05,"Workflow":0.02}}]}
